EXP 8: Create a Virtual Hard Disk and Allocate Storage
AIM:
To create a virtual hard disk and allocate storage using a Type-2 hypervisor.
PROCEDURE:
STEP 1: Select the created virtual machine.
STEP 2: Click on Edit Virtual Machine Settings.
STEP 3: Navigate to the Hard Disk / Storage option.
STEP 4: Click Add New Hard Disk.
STEP 5: Choose disk type (VDI / VMDK).
STEP 6: Select Dynamically Allocated storage.
STEP 7: Specify the disk size and click Finish.
STEP 8: Virtual hard disk is successfully created and allocated.

